    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-07-05T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-07-05T20:00:00-05:00" n="502"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d502">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">867N.01/7–446: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Truman</persName> to the
                        British Prime Minister</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Attlee</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="98" xml:id="d502fn98">Sent to London as Department’s
                        telegram 5213.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-07-05T21:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 5, 1946—9 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Personal. I fully appreciate the problems brought out in your message of July 4,
                    and in compliance with your wishes we are arranging that our committee and their
                    staff of 12 depart by air from Washington on Wednesday evening July 10. If there
                    are no delays en route they should be in London ready to start discussions on
                    Friday next.</p>
                <p>I would appreciate it very much if you could talk personally with Ambassador
                    Grady and Mr. Dorr upon their arrival.</p>
                <p>I join you in the hope we can reach an agreement on the main recommendations of
                    the report by the target date you mention.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harry Truman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
